SIMPLE: zircon
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zircon
<hw>Zir"con</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., the same word as
<ets>jargon</ets>. See <er>Jargon</er> a variety of zircon.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral consisting predominantly of
zirconium silicate (<chform>Zr2SiO4</chform>) occurring in tetragonal
crystals, usually of a brown or gray color. It consists of silica and
zirconia. A red variety, used as a gem, is called
<stype>hyacinth</stype>. Colorless, pale-yellow or smoky-brown varieties
from Ceylon are called <stype>jargon</stype>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>an imitation gemstone made of <cref>cubic
zirconia</cref>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Zircon syenite</b></col>, <cd>a coarse-grained syenite
containing zircon crystals and often also elaeolite. It is largely
developed in Southern Norway.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zircona</ent>⟦br⟧
